# Orion: local work → approved merge → Railway

## Local development

- Run the full stack: `npm run dev` (Postgres docker, API on **3001**, Vite on **5173** with `/api` proxy).
- First-time setup: `npm run setup`.
- Before opening a PR or pushing: `npm run check` (matches GitHub CI).
- Do **not** set `VITE_API_URL` locally unless debugging against a remote API.
- API env: copy `api/.env` from `api/.env.example`. Client: `client/.env` optional.

## Git and deploy (single path)

- **Only `main`** is deployed. There is no `staging` git branch and no Railway production environment.
- When the user says **deploy**, run `npm run deploy` (see `deploy-command.mdc`) — do not hand them manual git steps.
- **Never** use `railway up` for routine releases; deploys come from **git push to `main`** (GitHub → Railway auto-deploy).
- Railway environment is named `staging` (URLs `*-staging.up.railway.app`) but tracks **`main`** on GitHub.

## When changing hosting or CI

- Staging API URL for client builds: `https://orion-staging.up.railway.app` (`VITE_API_URL` on Railway `orion-client`).
